## 🚀 Setup Instructions

1. **Clone the Repository**

```bash
git clone https://github.com/your-username/chama-expense-tracker.git
cd chama-expense-tracker
Install JSON Server (if not already installed)

bash
Copy code
npm install -g json-server
Start the JSON Server

bash
Copy code
json-server --watch db.json
Open the App

Open index.html with Live Server (VS Code extension) or directly in a browser.

Make sure JSON Server is running on http://localhost:3000.

## 🗃️ db.json Structure
json
Copy code
{
  "members": [
    {
      "id": 1,
      "name": "Jane",
      "amount": 500,
      "description": "Monthly savings"
    }
  ],
  "expenses": [
    {
      "id": 1,
      "description": "Group trip to Naivasha",
      "amount": 300
    }
  ]
}
## 🔍 How Search Works
Enter a member's name in the top right search input.

Click the Search button to filter the displayed members.

It’s case-insensitive and partial matches work.

To clear the filter, empty the input and click Search again.

✏️ Customization Tips
💡 You can change the background image in index.html by editing the background-image inline style.

💰 You can modify currency display by replacing KES in index.js.

